# IT Task Assigner

Automated round-robin task assignment for IT engineering teams. Pulls tasks from Google Calendar, detects out-of-office engineers, assigns work in rotation, and notifies the team on Slack — all from a single HTML file with no backend required.

---

## What It Does

Each time you run it, the tool:

1. **Fetches tasks** from your HR Google Calendar for the target date
2. **Checks OOO status** by scanning each engineer's calendar for all-day events matching your configured keyword (e.g. `OOO`, `Out of Office`)
3. **Assigns tasks round-robin** — starting from the last engineer who received a task, rotating through the roster in order
4. **Skips OOO engineers** automatically and records who was skipped and why on each assignment card
5. **Notifies via Slack** — posts an individual message per assignment and a daily summary to your configured channel
6. **Advances the turn pointer** so the next run continues from where this one left off

---

## Setup

### Requirements
- An [Anthropic API key](https://console.anthropic.com/)
- A Google account with Google Calendar access (connected via Claude's Google Calendar integration)
- A Slack workspace connected via Claude's Slack integration

### Configuration Fields

| Field | Description | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Anthropic API Key | Your `sk-ant-...` key from Anthropic Console | `sk-ant-api03-...` |
| HR Calendar ID | The Google Calendar to pull tasks from | `hr-team@company.com` or `primary` |
| OOO Keyword | Text to detect in all-day events for OOO | `OOO` |
| Slack Channel | Channel to post assignment notifications | `#it-oncall` |
| Target Date | Date to run assignments for | `today` or `2025-06-10` |

### Engineer Roster

Add engineers using the input field in the sidebar. Format: `Full Name @slack.handle`

```
Alex Kim @alex.kim
Jordan Lee @jordan.lee
Sam Rivera @sam.rivera
```

Engineers are assigned in the order they appear in the list. The `NEXT` badge shows who is up for the next task. You can add or remove engineers at any time — the rotation continues from the current pointer.

---

## How Round-Robin Works

```
Run 1:  Task A → Alex    Task B → Jordan   Task C → Sam
Run 2:  Task A → Taylor  Task B → Alex     (Jordan = OOO, skipped)
Run 3:  Task A → Jordan  ...
```

The turn index persists across runs within the same session. OOO engineers are skipped for that day only — they resume in normal rotation on the next run.

---

## Slack Notifications

Each assignment generates a Slack message in this format:

```
📋 *Onboard new contractor* → assigned to *Alex Kim* (@alex.kim)
Time: 10:00 AM – 11:00 AM
Skipped: Jordan Lee (OOO)
```

At the end of a run, a summary is posted listing all assignments and any engineers who were out.

---

## Interface

- **Left sidebar** — configuration, roster management, run trigger
- **Main panel** — assignment cards per task, showing assignee, skipped engineers, and Slack status
- **Right panel** — live run log with timestamps, showing every calendar fetch, OOO check, and Slack post
- **Stats bar** — task count, assignments made, engineers skipped, Slack notifications sent

---

## Technical Notes

- Single-file HTML/CSS/JS — no build step, no server, no dependencies to install
- Calls the Anthropic API directly from the browser using `anthropic-dangerous-direct-browser-access`
- Uses Claude as the reasoning layer, with Google Calendar and Slack connected via MCP (Model Context Protocol)
- API key is never stored — enter it fresh each session
- Deploy to GitHub Pages, Netlify, or any static host — or just open locally in a browser

---

## Integrations

| Service | Purpose | MCP Server |
|---|---|---|
| Google Calendar | Fetch HR tasks + check engineer OOO | `calendarmcp.googleapis.com` |
| Slack | Post assignment notifications | `mcp.slack.com` |
| Anthropic API | AI reasoning layer (Claude Sonnet) | `api.anthropic.com` |

---

## Limitations

- OOO detection relies on all-day events containing your configured keyword in the title
- The turn index resets when the page is refreshed — note the current `NEXT` engineer before closing
- Google Calendar access depends on your Claude Google Calendar connection being active
- Designed for teams of 2–20 engineers
